<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1466,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,1546,1572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[328,447,1547,1572]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonapii">
<emphasis box="[328,447,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. tonapii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[665,814,1546,1572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="50" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">
Cook (
<number box="[745,806,1546,1572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from a single female specimen taken in Kerala State (
<collectingCountry box="[159,225,1586,1612]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">India</collectingCountry>
). The description of this species did not include a discussion of affinities. Furthermore Cook gave no information about the presence and number of swimming setae on II/III-L. The number and distribution of swimming setae on legs (see 
<tableCitation box="[496,584,1666,1692]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,239,155,179]" captionText="TABLE 5. Number of swimming setae of H. tonapii Cook." pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Table 
<number box="[568,584,1666,1692]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
</tableCitation>
), makes 
<taxonomicName box="[690,810,1667,1692]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonapii">
<emphasis box="[690,810,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. tonapii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic" authorityName="Pesic" box="[937,1151,1666,1692]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reinhardi">
<emphasis box="[937,1082,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. reinhardi</emphasis>
Pesic
</taxonomicName>
(Mediterranean) and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. wilesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[229,325,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[229,325,1706,1732]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see above). For a clearer separation of 
<taxonomicName box="[815,963,1707,1732]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reinhardi">
<emphasis box="[815,963,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. reinhardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1146,1707,1732]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonapii">
<emphasis box="[1024,1146,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. tonapii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, information on general variability of measurements in additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[801,920,1747,1772]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonapii">
<emphasis box="[801,920,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">H. tonapii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is necessary (
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic" box="[1083,1218,1746,1772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="50" refString="Pesic, V. (2002) Hydrodroma reinhardi n. sp., a new species of water mites (Acari, Actinedida, Hydrodromidae) from the Mediterranean area. Aquatic Insects, 24 (4), 317 - 325." type="journal article" year="2002">
Pesic 
<number box="[1154,1218,1746,1772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
